00073 static List
00074 List_new_list ()
00075 {
00076   List new_list;
00077 
00078   if (ListPool == NULL)
00079     {
00080       ListPool = L_create_alloc_pool ("_List", sizeof (_List), 8);
00081     }
00082 
00083   new_list = (List) L_alloc (ListPool);
00084   new_list->size = 0;
00085   new_list->first = NULL;
00086   new_list->last = NULL;
00087   new_list->current = (ListElement *) malloc (1 * sizeof (ListElement));
00088   if (new_list->current == NULL)
00089     I_punt ("L_new_list: malloc out of space");
00090   new_list->current[0] = NULL;
00091   new_list->num_currents = 1;
00092 
00093   return new_list;
00094 }

00364 List List_insert_first (List list, void *ptr)
00365 {
00366   List new_list = list;
00367   ListElement tmp;
00368 
00369   if (!new_list)
00370     {
00371       new_list = List_new_list ();
00372     }
00373   tmp = new_list->first;
00374   new_list->first = List_new_list_element ();
00375   if (tmp)
00376     {
00377       tmp->prev = new_list->first;
00378       new_list->first->next = tmp;
00379     }
00380   else
00381     {
00382       new_list->last = new_list->first;
00383     }
00384   new_list->first->ptr = ptr;
00385   new_list->size++;
00386 
00387   return new_list;
00388 }

00416 List List_insert_prev_l (List list, void *ptr, int level)
00417 {
00418   List new_list = list;
00419   ListElement tmp;
00420   ListElement new_element;
00421 
00422   if (!new_list)
00423     {
00424       new_list = List_new_list ();
00425     }
00426 
00427   if (level >= new_list->num_currents || level < 0)
00428     {
00429       I_punt ("List: Invalid pointer level");
00430     }
00431 
00432   /* 
00433    * When nothing is being pointed to, append to end of list 
00434    */
00435   if (!new_list->current[level])
00436     {
00437       tmp = new_list->last;
00438       new_list->last = List_new_list_element ();
00439       if (tmp)
00440         {
00441           tmp->next = new_list->last;
00442           new_list->last->prev = tmp;
00443         }
00444       else
00445         {
00446           new_list->first = new_list->last;
00447         }
00448       new_list->last->ptr = ptr;
00449       new_list->size++;
00450 
00451       return new_list;
00452     }
00453 
00454   tmp = new_list->current[level]->prev;
00455   new_element = List_new_list_element ();
00456   new_list->current[level]->prev = new_element;
00457   new_element->next = new_list->current[level];
00458   if (tmp)
00459     {
00460       tmp->next = new_element;
00461       new_element->prev = tmp;
00462     }
00463   else
00464     {
00465       new_list->first = new_element;
00466     }
00467   new_element->ptr = ptr;
00468   new_list->size++;

00470   return new_list;

00540 List List_append (List list, List append_list)
00541 {
00542   if (!list || list->size == 0)
00543     {
00544       List_reset (list);
00545       return append_list;
00546     }
00547 
00548   if (!append_list || append_list->size == 0)
00549     {
00550       List_reset (append_list);
00551       return list;
00552     }
00553 
00554   list->size += append_list->size;
00555   list->last->next = append_list->first;
00556   append_list->first->prev = list->last;
00557 
00558   list->last = append_list->last;
00559 
00560   return list;
00561 }

00564 List List_delete_current_l (List list, int level)
00565 {
00566   ListElement elem_old_curr;
00567   ListElement elem_old_next;
00568   ListElement elem_old_prev;
00569   int indx;
00570 
00571   if (!list)
00572     {
00573       return NULL;
00574     }
00575 
00576   if (level >= list->num_currents || level < 0)
00577     {
00578       I_punt ("List: Invalid pointer level");
00579     }
00580 
00581   if (!list->current[level])
00582     {
00583       return list;
00584     }
00585 
00586   elem_old_curr = list->current[level];
00587   elem_old_next = elem_old_curr->next;
00588   elem_old_prev = elem_old_curr->prev;
00589 
00590 
00591   /* Update all current pointers */
00592   for (indx = 0; indx < list->num_currents; indx++)
00593     {
00594       if (list->current[indx] == elem_old_curr)
00595         {
00596           list->current[indx] = elem_old_prev;
00597         }
00598     }
00599   if (elem_old_next)
00600     {
00601       elem_old_next->prev = elem_old_prev;
00602     }
00603   else
00604     {
00605       list->last = elem_old_prev;
00606     }
00607   if (elem_old_prev)
00608     {
00609       elem_old_prev->next = elem_old_next;
00610     }
00611   else
00612     {
00613       list->first = elem_old_next;
00614     }
00615 
00616   L_free (ListElementPool, elem_old_curr);
00617   list->size--;
00618   if (list->size == 0 && list->num_currents == 1)
00619     {
00620       return List_reset (list);
00621     }
00622   return list;
00623 }

00631 List List_reset (List list)
00632 {
00633   ListElement elem_ptr;
00634   ListElement elem_tmp;
00635 
00636   if (!list)
00637     {
00638       return NULL;
00639     }
00640 
00641   elem_ptr = list->first;
00642   while (elem_ptr)
00643     {
00644       elem_tmp = elem_ptr;
00645       elem_ptr = elem_ptr->next;
00646       L_free (ListElementPool, elem_tmp);
00647     }
00648   free (list->current);
00649   list->current = NULL;
00650   L_free (ListPool, list);
00651   return NULL;
00652 }

00654 List List_reset_free_ptrs (List list, void (*free_fn) (void *))
00655 {
00656   ListElement elem_ptr;
00657   ListElement elem_tmp;
00658 
00659   if (!list)
00660     {
00661       return NULL;
00662     }
00663 
00664   elem_ptr = list->first;
00665   while (elem_ptr)
00666     {
00667       elem_tmp = elem_ptr;
00668       elem_ptr = elem_ptr->next;
00669       (*free_fn) (elem_tmp->ptr);
00670       L_free (ListElementPool, elem_tmp);
00671     }
00672   free (list->current);
00673   L_free (ListPool, list);
00674   return NULL;
00675 }

00695 extern int
00696 List_register_new_ptr (List list)
00697 {
00698   ListElement *new_current;
00699   int indx;
00700 
00701   new_current =
00702     (ListElement *) malloc (sizeof (ListElement) * (list->num_currents + 1));
00703   if (new_current == NULL)
00704     I_punt ("L_register_new_ptr: malloc out of space");
00705 
00706   for (indx = 0; indx < list->num_currents; indx++)
00707     {
00708       new_current[indx] = list->current[indx];
00709     }
00710   new_current[list->num_currents] = NULL;
00711   list->num_currents++;
00712   free (list->current);
00713   list->current = new_current;
00714 
00715   return (list->num_currents - 1);
00716 }

00734 List List_remove (List list, void *ptr)
00735 {
00736   ListElement elem_old_curr;
00737   ListElement elem_old_next;
00738   ListElement elem_old_prev;
00739   int indx;
00740 
00741   if (!list)
00742     {
00743       return NULL;
00744     }
00745 
00746   for (elem_old_curr = list->first; elem_old_curr;
00747        elem_old_curr = elem_old_curr->next)
00748     {
00749       if (elem_old_curr->ptr == ptr)
00750         break;
00751     }
00752   if (!elem_old_curr)
00753     I_punt ("List_find_and_delete: Element not found.\n");
00754 
00755 
00756   elem_old_next = elem_old_curr->next;
00757   elem_old_prev = elem_old_curr->prev;
00758 
00759   /* Update all current pointers */
00760   for (indx = 0; indx < list->num_currents; indx++)
00761     {
00762       if (list->current[indx] == elem_old_curr)
00763         {
00764           list->current[indx] = elem_old_prev;
00765         }
00766     }
00767   if (elem_old_next)
00768     {
00769       elem_old_next->prev = elem_old_prev;
00770     }
00771   else
00772     {
00773       list->last = elem_old_prev;
00774     }
00775   if (elem_old_prev)
00776     {
00777       elem_old_prev->next = elem_old_next;
00778     }
00779   else
00780     {
00781       list->first = elem_old_next;
00782     }
00783 
00784   L_free (ListElementPool, elem_old_curr);
00785   list->size--;
00786   if (list->size == 0 && list->num_currents == 1)
00787     {
00788       return List_reset (list);
00789     }
00790   return list;
00791 }

00793 List
00794 List_copy (List list)
00795 {
00796   void *ptr;
00797   List ret = NULL;
00798   
00799   for (ptr = List_first (list); ptr; ptr = List_next (list))
00800     ret = List_insert_last (ret, ptr);
00801 
00802   return ret;
00803 }

00806 int
00807 List_member (List list, void *ptr)
00808 {
00809   ListElement elem_curr;
00810 
00811   if (!list)
00812     return 0;
00813 
00814   for (elem_curr = list->first; elem_curr; elem_curr = elem_curr->next)
00815     {
00816       if (elem_curr->ptr == ptr)
00817         break;
00818     }
00819   if (!elem_curr)
